Blocks.childText: NEW CHRISTIAN SOMETHING FOR JESUS. 6s & 4s. D. ROBERT LOWRY. Saviour, thy dying love Thou gavest me; Nor should I aught withhold, Dear Lord, from thee: In love my soul would bow, My heart fulfill its VOW, Some offering bring thee now, Something for thee, ae22.22 Copyright, 1871, by Biglow & Main. 583 SAVIOUR, thy dying love Help me the cross to bear, Thou gavest me; Thy wondrous love declare, Nor should I aught withhold, Some song to raise, or prayer- Dear Lord, from thee: Something for thee. In love my soul would bow, 3 Give me a faithful heart- My heart fulfill its vow, Likeness to thee- Some offering bring thee now- Something for thee. That each departing day Henceforth may see 2 O'er the blest mercy-seat, Some work of love begun, Pleading for me, Some deed of kindness done, My feeble faith looks up, Some wanderer sought and won- Jesus, to thee; Something for thee. S. D. PHELPS. JESUS, I WILL TRUST THEE. 6s & 5s. D. J. H. F. CC Jesus, I will trust thee, When across my soul, Like a fearful tempest, Doubts and fears shall roll. Rit. C - When the tempter cometh, Surely he will flee When I utter, Je-sus, I am trusting thee! 216
